@page "/reports/site-pnl"
@attribute [Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authorization.Authorize(Policy = NickFinance.WebApp.Identity.Permissions.ReportsView)]
@inject CurrentUser User
@rendermode InteractiveServer

<PageTitle>NickFinance · Site P&amp;L</PageTitle>

<NepPageHeader Title="Site-level P&L"
               Lede="Profit and loss broken out by physical site (Tema, Kotoka, Takoradi, Aflao, Paga, Elubo)." />

<NepCard Variant="warning">
    <h3>Pending kernel work</h3>
    <p>
        The site-level P&L report needs <code>site_id</code> as a first-class
        dimension on every <code>finance.ledger_event_lines</code> row. That column
        doesn't exist yet — the kernel currently only attaches site context at the
        source-entity level (Voucher, Float), not at the journal-line level.
    </p>
    <p>
        Adding it is a single migration plus a wiring change in
        <code>LedgerWriter.PostAsync</code> — see the feature backlog under
        "Site-level P&L". Until that lands, this page is a placeholder.
    </p>
    <p>
        For an interim view, use the
        <a href="/reports">existing P&L report</a> filtered by date range; site
        attribution is approximate (derived from the source voucher's float).
    </p>
</NepCard>

<NepEmpty Title="Site dimension not yet on ledger lines"
          Hint="Awaiting kernel migration. Use /reports for the legacy report." />
